      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <section id="section_ins_mxv_llb">
      <title>Converting JSON to YAML in Oxygen</title>
      <p id="p_m1g_cgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> includes a useful and simple tool for converting
        JSON files to YAML. The <uicontrol>JSON to YAML</uicontrol> action for invoking the tool can
        be found in the <menucascade product="developer editor json">
          <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
        </menucascade><menucascade product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
          <uicontrol>XML Tools</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> menu.</p>
      <p id="p_n1g_cgk_54b">To convert a JSON document to YAML, follow these steps:</p>
      <ol id="ol_o2q_dxv_llb">
        <li id="li_o1g_cgk_54b">
          <p id="p_p1g_cgk_54b">Select the <uicontrol>JSON to YAML</uicontrol> action from the
              <menucascade product="developer editor json">
              <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
            </menucascade><menucascade product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
              <uicontrol>XML Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
            </menucascade> menu.</p>
          <p id="p_q1g_cgk_54b">The <uicontrol>JSON to YAML</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed:</p>
          <p id="p_r1g_cgk_54b">
            <fig id="fig_p2q_dxv_llb">
              <title>JSON to YAML Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/json-to-yaml.png" id="image_q2q_dxv_llb"/>
            </fig>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li id="li_s1g_cgk_54b"> Choose or enter the <uicontrol>JSON URL</uicontrol> for the document you want to
          convert. </li>
        <li id="li_t1g_cgk_54b"> Choose the path of the <uicontrol>Output file</uicontrol> that will contain the
          resulting YAML document. </li>
        <li id="li_u1g_cgk_54b">
          <b>[Optional]</b> Select the <uicontrol>Open in Editor</uicontrol> option to open the
          resulting YAML document in the main editing pane. </li>
        <li id="li_v1g_cgk_54b"> Click the <uicontrol>Convert</uicontrol> button. </li>
      </ol>
      <p id="p_w1g_cgk_54b"><b>Result:</b> The original JSON document is now converted to a YAML document.</p>
    </section>
  </body>
